01:35.000 --> 01:40.000
Coaching

01:40.000 --> 01:44.000
So, the first one. What is coaching?

01:44.000 --> 01:47.000
The word is quite well-known.

01:47.000 --> 01:51.000
Surely, many have heard about it and even, perhaps, tried it somehow.

01:51.000 --> 01:54.000
But nevertheless, what is it?

01:54.000 --> 01:59.000
In fact, there is no definition of coaching.

01:59.000 --> 02:02.000
Each author tries to do it in his own way.

02:02.000 --> 02:08.000
Each author tries to introduce something of his own into the definition of this name.

02:08.000 --> 02:13.000
Nevertheless, each of those who tries to do it agrees on one thing.

02:13.000 --> 02:22.000
Namely, coaching is a method that helps to determine and achieve goals in the best way.

02:22.000 --> 02:30.000
This is a method that focuses on the result, on getting this result and on striving for the goal.

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
This is the most important thing.

02:32.000 --> 02:41.000
There are also many definitions that are quite cumbersome, which may not be quite understandable.

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
But nevertheless, I would like to emphasize one thing.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
This is a method of determining and achieving goals.

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
And with minimal effort to achieve the maximum results.

02:51.000 --> 02:59.000
And now I would like to talk to you about how to build a relationship in coaching.

03:00.000 --> 03:06.000
How to build a relationship between a coach and a nurse?

03:06.000 --> 03:18.000
After all, it is really very important, in fact, if a coach has confidence that every person has a huge potential.

03:18.000 --> 03:25.000
That every person is a creator and he already has the maximum opportunities.

03:25.000 --> 03:29.000
This is a very important coach's confidence.

03:29.000 --> 03:33.000
Without this confidence, you probably should not even do coaching.

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
And then.

03:35.000 --> 03:41.000
A very important point is mutual trust between the coach and his nurse.

03:41.000 --> 03:50.000
Because if there is no mutual understanding, if there is no trust between these two people, then the coaching process will not work.

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
It will be anything but coaching.

03:54.000 --> 04:04.000
Moreover, it is very important that if the coach and his nurse interact, there should be mutual trust between them.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
This is necessary.

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
And another very important point.

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
After all, coaching is not a direct approach.

04:11.000 --> 04:16.000
This is a rather soft style.

04:16.000 --> 04:22.000
And for the manager, for the coach, maybe not everyone will like it.

04:23.000 --> 04:30.000
Rather, it is a very important and valuable quality of a coach, which is external in the organization.

04:30.000 --> 04:34.000
Or it is a coach who works inside the company and supports this style.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.000
The style of non-directivity.

04:36.000 --> 04:46.000
And another very important point is that in coaching, a professional coach does not give advice.

04:47.000 --> 04:50.000
He guides and asks questions.

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
But in no case is he an expert.

04:53.000 --> 04:59.000
There is such a direction as expert coaching, which we will talk about in the future.

04:59.000 --> 05:05.000
But nevertheless, I would like to emphasize once again that a coach is not the one who gives advice.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.000
This is not the one who gives instructions.

05:07.000 --> 05:17.000
This is the one who listens to you and asks special questions in order to clarify the goal that is important for you.

05:17.000 --> 05:21.000
To outline certain steps and ways to achieve this goal.

05:21.000 --> 05:28.000
Next, I would like to point out that in coaching we do not focus on problems.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
We are talking about tasks.

05:30.000 --> 05:33.000
This is a big and fundamental difference.

05:34.000 --> 05:40.000
Because coaching is aimed at the action now, at the action in the future.

05:40.000 --> 05:44.000
And in no case at how it was in the past.

05:44.000 --> 05:52.000
Remember, we live now and we think about how we will achieve our goals in the future.

05:52.000 --> 06:00.000
Therefore, a very important point is that the focus is on the present and the focus is on the future.

06:01.000 --> 06:07.000
And here it is very important for us that we do not think about what mistakes we made before.

06:07.000 --> 06:11.000
We forget what we did or did not do before.

06:11.000 --> 06:23.000
The focus is on the goal and the focus is on what we can do to improve our activity and to achieve the goal that we strive for.

06:24.000 --> 06:28.000
It happens very often that the nanny says,

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
I don't want to be late for work anymore.

06:31.000 --> 06:36.000
I don't want to watch my subordinates not doing their job anymore.

06:36.000 --> 06:40.000
And when you ask the question, what do you want?

06:40.000 --> 06:48.000
Then the answer is again, I don't want my subordinates to behave this way.

06:48.000 --> 06:52.000
Okay, what do you want?

06:52.000 --> 06:58.000
And then the coaching begins, when the manager says, I want them to come on time.

06:58.000 --> 07:02.000
This is the focus on the task.

07:02.000 --> 07:07.000
We focus on the problem, on what I don't want.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
And we focus our attention on the task.

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
What do I want?

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
What do I want to achieve?

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
What task do I want to solve?

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
And what goal do I want to achieve?

07:19.000 --> 07:25.000
Another very important principle of coaching is confidentiality.

07:25.000 --> 07:28.000
If the coach is working with his client,

07:28.000 --> 07:35.000
then there must be a 100% guarantee that all the information that the coach received from his client,

07:35.000 --> 07:38.000
from his subordinate, will remain between them.

07:38.000 --> 07:48.000
Unless it was discussed in advance that any parts of the information provided to the coach can be disclosed to the client.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
Otherwise, there is no way.

07:50.000 --> 07:56.000
That is, our rule is this, compliance with absolute and complete confidentiality.

07:56.000 --> 08:07.000
Only in these conditions can our client, our subordinate, be absolutely sure that he can tell us everything he wants.

08:07.000 --> 08:13.000
And he can be absolutely calm that it will remain between him and the coach.

08:13.000 --> 08:16.000
This is, you know, similar to the relationship of friends.

08:16.000 --> 08:20.000
Because when I trust a friend with some important information,

08:20.000 --> 08:26.000
I want to be sure that this information will remain between us and that no one else will find out about it.

08:26.000 --> 08:28.000
That is why I can trust him.

08:28.000 --> 08:35.000
Our task is to become the same friends at this moment for our subordinate,

08:35.000 --> 08:40.000
so that he opens up and has the opportunity to trust us completely.

08:40.000 --> 08:45.000
And he was absolutely sure that absolute confidentiality was guaranteed to him.

08:45.000 --> 08:54.000
So, we, professional coaches, use the concept of basic coaching in our work.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
What is it?

08:56.000 --> 09:02.000
We are deeply confident that every person has a very great potential.

09:02.000 --> 09:08.000
So great that sometimes it is even difficult to realize what we can and what we can.

09:08.000 --> 09:11.000
But nevertheless, what prevents us?

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
These are obstacles.

09:13.000 --> 09:17.000
And not so much external obstacles, but rather internal ones.

09:17.000 --> 09:21.000
This is some kind of uncertainty, this is fear to act.

09:21.000 --> 09:26.000
It is possible, on the contrary, to like the aspiration, to make an impression,

09:26.000 --> 09:31.000
which at a certain moment can block our abilities.

09:31.000 --> 09:39.000
Remember when fear blocked your knowledge at the same exam or at the same test?

09:39.000 --> 09:46.000
Remember when you wanted to make some great impression, and suddenly it didn't work out?

09:46.000 --> 09:55.000
It's just that your potential was lower than usual due to the fact that you felt internal obstacles.

09:55.000 --> 10:03.000
So, the goal of coaching is to minimize these obstacles and maximize potential.

10:03.000 --> 10:09.000
To increase potential by reducing obstacles, both internal and external.

10:09.000 --> 10:12.000
What do we mean when we say external obstacles?

10:12.000 --> 10:18.000
External obstacles can be elementary, at work, if so.

10:18.000 --> 10:24.000
I can't move up the career ladder because I don't have an education or something else.

10:24.000 --> 10:29.000
But all these issues are quite solvable and all these obstacles can be overcome.

10:29.000 --> 10:34.000
And a coach has the right to instill this confidence in his subordinate.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.000
Yes, you can overcome it.

10:36.000 --> 10:44.000
Yes, it is such an obstacle that may seem difficult now, but in the future you will definitely overcome it.

