11:25.000 --> 11:29.000
So, what are the goals of coaching?

11:29.000 --> 11:34.000
We have already discussed what coaching is and what are its goals.

11:34.000 --> 11:42.000
The goal of coaching in a company, in business processes, is, first of all, to achieve the result.

11:42.000 --> 11:48.000
To achieve the goal, the one that was initially stated.

11:49.000 --> 11:55.000
It is very important for us to understand that there are goals, there are goals for goals,

11:55.000 --> 12:03.000
and in each goal there are certain small goals that we must pass in order to get to the desired state.

12:03.000 --> 12:12.000
There is a desired state and there is a starting state from which we want to move to the desired state.

12:12.000 --> 12:21.000
The goal of coaching is to help a person move from where he is now to where he wants to be.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
The same is true for a company.

12:23.000 --> 12:27.000
A company that wants to move to a new high-quality state,

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
that wants to make certain changes,

12:30.000 --> 12:35.000
invites a coach to stimulate these changes,

12:35.000 --> 12:39.000
to achieve the result that it would like.

12:40.000 --> 12:43.000
And so we can summarize.

12:43.000 --> 12:46.000
A coach does not give advice.

12:46.000 --> 12:52.000
A coach will not tell you what, how and in what order to do it.

12:52.000 --> 12:55.000
A coach is not the person who will come to your company,

12:55.000 --> 12:59.000
do everything himself and you will only have to reap the fruits.

12:59.000 --> 13:01.000
Rather, not like that.

13:01.000 --> 13:04.000
Let's remember Socrates.

13:05.000 --> 13:11.000
He said that he was a money-grubbing grandmother of knowledge.

13:11.000 --> 13:17.000
I can help you to learn, but I cannot force you to do it.

13:17.000 --> 13:19.000
The same is true here.

13:19.000 --> 13:24.000
Coaching is very close to the expression of Socrates.

13:24.000 --> 13:28.000
A coach can contribute to the education and development,

13:28.000 --> 13:33.000
but he cannot do this development and education for you.

13:33.000 --> 13:37.000
He can stimulate you, he can cheer you up,

13:37.000 --> 13:40.000
he can motivate you,

13:40.000 --> 13:45.000
he can develop a plan and control of all these actions with you.

13:45.000 --> 13:48.000
But the actions will be for you.

13:48.000 --> 13:51.000
For the person who turned to the coach

13:51.000 --> 13:56.000
or for the company that turned to the coach to make changes.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
Let's talk about the development in coaching.

13:59.000 --> 14:04.000
In fact, the goal of coaching is the resultiveness of achieving the goal.

14:04.000 --> 14:07.000
And yet, what else is going on?

14:07.000 --> 14:14.000
Coaching allows you to develop awareness, responsibility and self-confidence.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.000
Let's imagine,

14:16.000 --> 14:21.000
only what we are aware of, we can control.

14:22.000 --> 14:28.000
Only what we take responsibility for is our decision.

14:28.000 --> 14:34.000
This is the decision that we have made for ourselves and that we are obliged to fulfill.

14:34.000 --> 14:40.000
It often happens that the head assigns certain tasks to his subordinates,

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
and he ignores them.

14:42.000 --> 14:45.000
Why? Why doesn't he take responsibility for himself?

14:45.000 --> 14:52.000
And he can take responsibility only when he is internally agreeable with this decision,

14:52.000 --> 14:54.000
when he himself wants to fulfill it,

14:54.000 --> 14:57.000
and then he will do it in the best way.

14:57.000 --> 14:59.000
And this is one of the tasks of coaching.

14:59.000 --> 15:05.000
To make a person take responsibility for the task assigned to him

15:05.000 --> 15:08.000
and to fulfill it in the best way.

15:09.000 --> 15:14.000
Another important point that we also talked about is the development of self-confidence.

15:14.000 --> 15:20.000
Only a person who is confident in himself is capable of great achievements.

15:20.000 --> 15:24.000
A person who realizes his resources,

15:24.000 --> 15:27.000
who realizes his goals,

15:27.000 --> 15:30.000
who takes responsibility for his achievements,

15:30.000 --> 15:34.000
is really a person who can achieve his goals

15:34.000 --> 15:38.000
and who is stimulated and inspired by these goals

15:38.000 --> 15:42.000
and makes this path to the goal attractive.

15:43.000 --> 15:46.000
This is also motivation.

15:46.000 --> 15:51.000
That's why I would like to stop at the moment

15:51.000 --> 15:54.000
what is coaching and who is a coach?

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
And how is it different from the rest?

15:56.000 --> 16:01.000
Coaching is a method that came to us from sports,

16:01.000 --> 16:03.000
from sports training.

16:03.000 --> 16:07.000
In English, it means coaching.

16:07.000 --> 16:10.000
It is individual coaching.

16:11.000 --> 16:14.000
Coaching is to achieve a certain result.

16:14.000 --> 16:17.000
A coach can be called a coach,

16:17.000 --> 16:21.000
but this concept is much broader.

16:21.000 --> 16:28.000
And that's why the word coaching is not translated into Russian.

16:28.000 --> 16:32.000
In our Russian language, we have not yet come up with a term

16:32.000 --> 16:36.000
that could replace the word coaching.

16:36.000 --> 16:39.000
Coaching is not mentorship.

16:39.000 --> 16:41.000
It is not mentorship.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
It is not coaching.

16:43.000 --> 16:46.000
It is exactly coaching.

16:46.000 --> 16:50.000
This is the coaching that we have just discussed.

16:50.000 --> 16:56.000
This is a method that allows you to determine and achieve goals.

16:56.000 --> 17:01.000
It is a coach who stimulates you to achieve these goals.

17:01.000 --> 17:05.000
It is a coach who inspires you to achieve these goals.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.000
But he does not give advice.

17:07.000 --> 17:09.000
If it is an external coach,

17:09.000 --> 17:13.000
if it is an internal coach who works with the manager.

17:13.000 --> 17:15.000
We will also talk about the topic

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
when a coach is a manager

17:18.000 --> 17:22.000
and how he can build this coaching interaction.

17:28.000 --> 17:30.000
So, coach management.

17:30.000 --> 17:33.000
Our next topic.

17:34.000 --> 17:39.000
Let's think about how it differs from just management.

17:39.000 --> 17:41.000
Management is management.

17:41.000 --> 17:45.000
And what is coach management?

17:45.000 --> 17:49.000
First of all, the basis of coach management is

17:49.000 --> 17:56.000
that questions gradually come to replace the directives.

17:57.000 --> 18:03.000
Or it is a combination of directions with additional questions.

18:04.000 --> 18:08.000
When a manager gives a task to a subordinate,

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
one of his tasks is to check

18:10.000 --> 18:15.000
how true his subordinate understood this task.

18:15.000 --> 18:18.000
How much resources he has now

18:18.000 --> 18:22.000
in order to complete this task.

18:23.000 --> 18:25.000
And what can help this subordinate

18:25.000 --> 18:29.000
to approach this task even more responsibly,

18:29.000 --> 18:32.000
with even more full return.

18:32.000 --> 18:36.000
So, coach management is based on the fact

18:36.000 --> 18:43.000
that more and more questions should come to replace the directions.

18:43.000 --> 18:48.000
And we mostly ask open questions in coaching.

18:48.000 --> 18:53.000
You know the difference between open and closed questions.

18:53.000 --> 18:55.000
Open questions are those

18:55.000 --> 19:00.000
that are unlikely to be answered unambiguously.

19:00.000 --> 19:03.000
Open questions stimulate.

19:03.000 --> 19:11.000
Open questions encourage to give a detailed and full answer.

19:11.000 --> 19:17.000
They stimulate us to think and be active.

19:17.000 --> 19:19.000
So, let's summarize.

19:19.000 --> 19:23.000
What does a coach do?

19:23.000 --> 19:27.000
First of all, he gives a task to his subordinate

19:27.000 --> 19:29.000
and asks questions.

19:29.000 --> 19:32.000
How clear is the task?

19:32.000 --> 19:35.000
Does the subordinate have all the resources

19:35.000 --> 19:38.000
and necessary funds to complete this task?

19:38.000 --> 19:44.000
How does the subordinate plan to complete this task?

19:45.000 --> 19:48.000
And what is the deadline?

19:48.000 --> 19:52.000
Of course, there should be good and wonderful interaction

19:52.000 --> 19:57.000
and trust between the coach and his subordinate.

19:57.000 --> 20:03.000
Otherwise, the coach will not get a sincere answer from the subordinate.

20:03.000 --> 20:06.000
If there is trust in the relationship

20:06.000 --> 20:09.000
between the coach and the subordinate,

20:10.000 --> 20:13.000
then by giving the task to the subordinate

20:13.000 --> 20:16.000
and asking him about the results

20:16.000 --> 20:19.000
and how much it is feasible for him,

20:19.000 --> 20:23.000
the coach can get the following answer.

20:23.000 --> 20:27.000
I don't have the resources now.

20:27.000 --> 20:31.000
I don't quite understand this task.

20:31.000 --> 20:36.000
If the coach can clarify his task,

20:36.000 --> 20:40.000
if he can give the opportunity to this person

20:40.000 --> 20:43.000
to find time to complete the task,

20:43.000 --> 20:48.000
then most likely the task will be successful.

20:48.000 --> 20:51.000
I want to emphasize once again

20:51.000 --> 20:54.000
that only in the relationship of trust

20:54.000 --> 20:57.000
between the coach and his subordinate

20:57.000 --> 21:00.000
it is possible that this process will go smoothly

21:00.000 --> 21:05.000
and the goal will be more effective.

21:05.000 --> 21:10.000
The task of any coach, including the coach,

21:10.000 --> 21:13.000
is to maintain control,

21:13.000 --> 21:17.000
that is, to control how the task is performed,

21:17.000 --> 21:20.000
to highlight certain points

21:20.000 --> 21:24.000
after which the subordinate should receive feedback

21:24.000 --> 21:28.000
and talk about the progress in this project.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.000
It is perfectly clear that the coach

21:32.000 --> 21:35.000
should perform his functions,

21:35.000 --> 21:38.000
issue orders,

21:38.000 --> 21:42.000
use questions and control the activity.

21:42.000 --> 21:45.000
These are the necessary conditions.

21:45.000 --> 21:49.000
So, the coach manager should have an adequate idea

21:49.000 --> 21:53.000
whether his subordinate is ready for the coaching.

21:53.000 --> 21:56.000
If we are talking about the coaching,

21:56.000 --> 21:59.000
we will see that there are newbies

21:59.000 --> 22:02.000
who come to our organization

22:02.000 --> 22:06.000
and who most likely need to receive instructions.

22:06.000 --> 22:10.000
They want to be told and shown what to do.

22:10.000 --> 22:13.000
And most likely for such people

22:13.000 --> 22:16.000
it is necessary to have a coach.

22:16.000 --> 22:19.000
And this is a very important point.

22:19.000 --> 22:23.000
The coach should be able to give the necessary feedback

22:23.000 --> 22:26.000
and to tell what needs to be done.

22:26.000 --> 22:29.000
And most likely for such people

22:29.000 --> 22:32.000
coaching is not quite appropriate.

22:32.000 --> 22:35.000
For them, a tool such as instructions,

22:35.000 --> 22:39.000
explanations and mentorship will be more suitable.

22:39.000 --> 22:42.000
It will be very good if a person has a mentor

22:42.000 --> 22:45.000
who will take him to his position step by step,

22:45.000 --> 22:48.000
tell him and show him what to do

22:48.000 --> 22:51.000
in the conditions of this organization.

22:51.000 --> 22:54.000
And then his work will be successful.

22:54.000 --> 22:57.000
There are other types of employees.

22:57.000 --> 23:01.000
For example, an employee who is already a specialist.

23:01.000 --> 23:04.000
He already knows the working conditions well enough,

23:04.000 --> 23:07.000
he already does a lot on his own,

23:07.000 --> 23:10.000
he is already motivated enough to work,

23:10.000 --> 23:14.000
and he can already apply coaching methods.

23:14.000 --> 23:18.000
In order to specify what he can do even better,

23:19.000 --> 23:22.000
how he can improve his activity.

23:22.000 --> 23:25.000
And here the task of the manager is to control

23:25.000 --> 23:28.000
and direct this employee

23:28.000 --> 23:31.000
in order for him to reach a new level of his development.

23:31.000 --> 23:34.000
Develop in this organization,

23:34.000 --> 23:37.000
realizing his resources, his advantages,

23:37.000 --> 23:40.000
and working on his disadvantages.

23:40.000 --> 23:43.000
And the third category of employees

23:43.000 --> 23:46.000
is the employees who are already experienced.

23:47.000 --> 23:50.000
These are, so to speak, old-timers

23:50.000 --> 23:53.000
