43:15.000 --> 43:18.000
to change and improvement exist?

43:18.000 --> 43:21.000
One of such elements is

43:21.000 --> 43:24.000
dissatisfaction with the current situation.

43:25.000 --> 43:28.000
This is one of the key elements.

43:28.000 --> 43:31.000
If you are satisfied with everything,

43:31.000 --> 43:34.000
if your company is doing great

43:34.000 --> 43:37.000
and you don't want to change anything,

43:37.000 --> 43:40.000
changes will happen

43:40.000 --> 43:43.000
as they say, with a creak.

43:43.000 --> 43:46.000
These changes will be less effective

43:46.000 --> 43:49.000
than we'd like,

43:49.000 --> 43:52.000
and maybe not necessary.

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
The basic thing we should say

43:55.000 --> 43:58.000
is dissatisfaction with the current situation.

43:58.000 --> 44:01.000
Next,

44:01.000 --> 44:04.000
it's understanding how important

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
this change is and what it will lead to.

44:07.000 --> 44:10.000
If we understand that

44:10.000 --> 44:13.000
the same service system

44:13.000 --> 44:16.000
will make it easier

44:16.000 --> 44:19.000
to track the base,

44:19.000 --> 44:22.000
to communicate with clients,

44:22.000 --> 44:25.000
to simplify the turnover system,

44:25.000 --> 44:28.000
these are all advantages.

44:28.000 --> 44:31.000
Tell your employees about these advantages.

44:31.000 --> 44:34.000
Explain to them why it's so important.

44:34.000 --> 44:37.000
This is the second element.

44:37.000 --> 44:40.000
Understanding the goal,

44:40.000 --> 44:43.000
what we are making these changes for.

44:43.000 --> 44:46.000
The third element is a clear action plan.

44:46.000 --> 44:49.000
These are planned steps

44:49.000 --> 44:52.000
to achieve the goal.

44:52.000 --> 44:55.000
What should we do?

44:55.000 --> 44:58.000
What steps should we take

44:58.000 --> 45:01.000
to reach the goal?

45:01.000 --> 45:04.000
Of course,

45:04.000 --> 45:07.000
the sum of these three elements,

45:07.000 --> 45:10.000
dissatisfaction with the current situation,

45:10.000 --> 45:13.000
a clear goal and a plan,

45:13.000 --> 45:16.000
these three elements should be more important.

45:16.000 --> 45:19.000
They should be stronger

45:19.000 --> 45:22.000
than the desire to be a status quo

45:22.000 --> 45:25.000
and to act in the old way.

45:25.000 --> 45:28.000
This is a good tool for the manager

45:28.000 --> 45:31.000
to implement these tools of change,

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
to act more actively

45:34.000 --> 45:37.000
and to understand what we are doing.

45:37.000 --> 45:40.000
As we said,

45:41.000 --> 45:44.000
only what is realized,

45:44.000 --> 45:47.000
only what a person really wants to do,

45:47.000 --> 45:50.000
he will do.

45:50.000 --> 45:53.000
If this is not the case,

45:53.000 --> 45:56.000
we can only stimulate this person to achieve.

45:56.000 --> 45:59.000
But we cannot force him.

45:59.000 --> 46:02.000
You know, there is an expression,

46:02.000 --> 46:05.000
you can bring a horse to the pond,

46:05.000 --> 46:08.000
but it is impossible to force it to drink.

46:08.000 --> 46:11.000
So,

46:11.000 --> 46:14.000
we should be guided by this formula of change.

46:14.000 --> 46:17.000
I will repeat it again.

46:17.000 --> 46:20.000
Dissatisfaction with the current situation,

46:20.000 --> 46:23.000
a clear goal and a plan.

46:23.000 --> 46:26.000
These are the things we need to implement changes.

46:26.000 --> 46:29.000
Now we will talk about the coaching steps

46:29.000 --> 46:32.000
in organizational changes.

46:32.000 --> 46:35.000
The first thing to say

46:35.000 --> 46:38.000
is that we should be prepared for the diagnosis.

46:38.000 --> 46:41.000
Before implementing something new in the organization,

46:41.000 --> 46:44.000
including coaching,

46:44.000 --> 46:47.000
we should understand

46:47.000 --> 46:50.000
how ready the organization is for it,

46:50.000 --> 46:53.000
what organizational changes are planned to be implemented,

46:53.000 --> 46:56.000
and how ready the employees are for coach management.

46:56.000 --> 46:59.000
The second point of this program

46:59.000 --> 47:02.000
is coaching for determining goals.

47:02.000 --> 47:05.000
We have already discussed this point,

47:05.000 --> 47:08.000
but now we will discuss it in more detail.

47:08.000 --> 47:11.000
The third point is planning.

47:11.000 --> 47:14.000
Coaching at the planning stage.

47:14.000 --> 47:17.000
And the fourth stage is feedback.

47:17.000 --> 47:20.000
Feedback to both the supervisor

47:20.000 --> 47:23.000
and the supervisor

47:23.000 --> 47:26.000
in the sense that

47:26.000 --> 47:29.000
the supervisor is not the only one

47:29.000 --> 47:32.000
who is responsible for the changes.

47:32.000 --> 47:35.000
The coach is also responsible for the changes.

47:35.000 --> 47:38.000
The supervisor is responsible for the changes.

47:38.000 --> 47:41.000
These are the four basic blocks

47:41.000 --> 47:44.000
that we will regulate in the system

47:44.000 --> 47:47.000
that needs to be changed.

47:47.000 --> 47:50.000
The company itself

47:50.000 --> 47:53.000
should determine

47:53.000 --> 47:56.000
what changes are needed,

47:56.000 --> 47:59.000
what changes are needed now,

47:59.000 --> 48:02.000
and accordingly invite the coach,

48:02.000 --> 48:05.000
who will be able to determine

48:05.000 --> 48:08.000
the important points

48:08.000 --> 48:11.000
that concern coaching.

48:11.000 --> 48:14.000
I would like to draw your attention

48:14.000 --> 48:17.000
to the next slide,

48:17.000 --> 48:20.000
where we will see how to apply coaching

48:20.000 --> 48:23.000
at the analysis stage.

48:23.000 --> 48:26.000
At this stage, the coach asks a number of questions.

48:26.000 --> 48:29.000
These may be questions like

48:29.000 --> 48:32.000
What is the sphere of the organization's activity

48:32.000 --> 48:35.000
or the team's division

48:35.000 --> 48:38.000
or the committee's needs

48:38.000 --> 48:41.000
in the changes above all?

48:41.000 --> 48:44.000
Why are the changes in this area so important?

48:44.000 --> 48:47.000
How will the changes in the selected sphere

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
affect the other areas of the company's activity?

48:50.000 --> 48:53.000
Why are these changes needed now?

48:53.000 --> 48:56.000
Are the selected structures ready for the changes?

48:56.000 --> 48:59.000
What consequences can there be

48:59.000 --> 49:02.000
due to the implementation of these changes?

49:02.000 --> 49:05.000
It is natural that there are a lot of questions

49:05.000 --> 49:08.000
that should be asked at the diagnostic stage.

49:08.000 --> 49:11.000
But first of all,

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
the supervisor, who wishes to implement

49:14.000 --> 49:17.000
the changes,

49:17.000 --> 49:20.000
should answer these questions.

49:20.000 --> 49:23.000
If we consider an example

49:23.000 --> 49:26.000
from a trading company,

49:26.000 --> 49:29.000
where the supervisor invited a coach

49:29.000 --> 49:32.000
to implement the changes in his company,

49:32.000 --> 49:35.000
what can be done better?

49:35.000 --> 49:38.000
He already had experience

49:38.000 --> 49:41.000
in implementing changes,

49:41.000 --> 49:44.000
both successful and not so successful,

49:44.000 --> 49:47.000
and at this stage he decided

49:47.000 --> 49:50.000
to use the help and support of the coach.

49:50.000 --> 49:53.000
What did we do at this stage?

49:53.000 --> 49:56.000
We asked him questions.

49:56.000 --> 49:59.000
Which sphere of the company's activity

49:59.000 --> 50:02.000
should be changed first?

50:02.000 --> 50:05.000
Perhaps, by changing something

50:05.000 --> 50:08.000
in this system of the organization,

50:08.000 --> 50:11.000
you can influence the change.

50:11.000 --> 50:14.000
He mentioned several categories

50:14.000 --> 50:17.000
that need to be changed in his company.

50:17.000 --> 50:20.000
In particular,

50:20.000 --> 50:23.000
it was the qualification of the staff

50:23.000 --> 50:26.000
who worked in the sales department.

50:26.000 --> 50:29.000
His qualification of these employees

50:29.000 --> 50:32.000
did not quite suit him.

50:32.000 --> 50:35.000
And, accordingly,

50:35.000 --> 50:38.000
it was one of the main tasks

50:39.000 --> 50:42.000
that he wanted to solve.

50:42.000 --> 50:45.000
But he had no idea

50:45.000 --> 50:48.000
how to do it.

50:48.000 --> 50:51.000
Of course, there were tasks

50:51.000 --> 50:54.000
that were in line with this.

50:54.000 --> 50:57.000
It was the increase of motivation

50:57.000 --> 51:00.000
of the employees and the achievement

51:00.000 --> 51:03.000
of new goals.

51:03.000 --> 51:06.000
But first of all,

51:06.000 --> 51:09.000
what could he do

51:09.000 --> 51:12.000
to make the processes

51:12.000 --> 51:15.000
in this department more effective?

51:15.000 --> 51:18.000
What could he do

51:18.000 --> 51:21.000
to make the processes

51:21.000 --> 51:24.000
in this department more effective?

51:24.000 --> 51:27.000
So that the employees

51:27.000 --> 51:30.000
could better cope with their duties.

51:30.000 --> 51:33.000
Here, of course,

51:33.000 --> 51:36.000
we came to the conclusion

51:36.000 --> 51:39.000
that instead of the new employees

51:39.000 --> 51:42.000
who would naturally be associated

51:42.000 --> 51:45.000
with new costs,

51:45.000 --> 51:48.000
we should work with those

51:48.000 --> 51:51.000
who are already there.

51:51.000 --> 51:54.000
We should work with those people

51:54.000 --> 51:57.000
who are already in the department.

51:57.000 --> 52:00.000
We should stimulate them to work.

52:01.000 --> 52:04.000
Some of these employees

52:04.000 --> 52:07.000
needed to be trained.

52:07.000 --> 52:10.000
For some of them,

52:10.000 --> 52:13.000
we should have given instructions

52:13.000 --> 52:16.000
as for new employees.

52:16.000 --> 52:19.000
For some of them,

52:19.000 --> 52:22.000
we should have stimulated them

52:22.000 --> 52:25.000
by changing their motivation.

52:25.000 --> 52:28.000
As a result, the head came to the conclusion

52:28.000 --> 52:31.000
that the motivation for these employees

52:31.000 --> 52:34.000
should be varied.

52:34.000 --> 52:37.000
And together we have chosen

52:37.000 --> 52:40.000
such a system of motivation

52:40.000 --> 52:43.000
that was really adequate

52:43.000 --> 52:46.000
at this stage of development.

52:46.000 --> 52:49.000
Which could really stimulate

52:49.000 --> 52:52.000
these employees to work better.

52:52.000 --> 52:55.000
From the conversation of the employees

52:55.000 --> 52:58.000
I can say that the new employees

52:58.000 --> 53:01.000
are not satisfied with the new instructions.

53:01.000 --> 53:04.000
The instructions that were sent down

53:04.000 --> 53:07.000
were not always acceptable.

53:07.000 --> 53:10.000
But as you understand,

53:10.000 --> 53:13.000
quite often the managers

53:13.000 --> 53:16.000
do not ask how much you like it.

53:16.000 --> 53:19.000
They send instructions

53:19.000 --> 53:22.000
and then face difficulties.

53:22.000 --> 53:25.000
And the coaching approach

53:25.000 --> 53:28.000
helps to find the compromise

53:28.000 --> 53:31.000
when the manager is satisfied

53:31.000 --> 53:34.000
with the way the employees work

53:34.000 --> 53:37.000
and with their motivation.

53:37.000 --> 53:40.000
And the employees are satisfied

53:40.000 --> 53:43.000
with the system that was built.

53:43.000 --> 53:46.000
In particular,

53:46.000 --> 53:49.000
we conducted team coaching

53:50.000 --> 53:53.000
where these employees

53:53.000 --> 53:56.000
conducted some kind of brainstorming

53:56.000 --> 53:59.000
in the presence of their manager.

53:59.000 --> 54:02.000
The employees themselves determined

54:02.000 --> 54:05.000
what their motivation would be.

54:05.000 --> 54:08.000
What would they like to have?

54:08.000 --> 54:11.000
How would they like to work?

54:11.000 --> 54:14.000
And what motivation would they like to have?

54:14.000 --> 54:17.000
It's a multi-stage process.

54:18.000 --> 54:21.000
And it was quite successful.

54:21.000 --> 54:24.000
The manager and the employees

54:24.000 --> 54:27.000
were satisfied.

54:27.000 --> 54:30.000
It's one of those moments

54:30.000 --> 54:33.000
when everyone wins.

54:33.000 --> 54:36.000
The manager and the employees.

54:36.000 --> 54:39.000
But the organization also wins.

54:39.000 --> 54:42.000
The organization gets more profit.

54:42.000 --> 54:45.000
It gets loyal employees.

54:45.000 --> 54:48.000
It gets employees

54:48.000 --> 54:51.000
who are ready to work here.

54:53.000 --> 54:56.000
Employees who won't leave the company.

54:57.000 --> 55:00.000
They created their own motivation.

55:00.000 --> 55:03.000
It all came from them.

55:03.000 --> 55:06.000
These are the employees

55:06.000 --> 55:09.000
who will stay in the organization.

55:09.000 --> 55:12.000
Because besides the material factors

55:12.000 --> 55:15.000
there are also non-material factors.

55:15.000 --> 55:18.000
The employees felt more free here.

55:18.000 --> 55:21.000
They felt respected.

55:21.000 --> 55:24.000
They were considered.

55:24.000 --> 55:27.000
And it's good enough.

55:27.000 --> 55:30.000
Because directives don't always work.

55:30.000 --> 55:33.000
Directives nowadays

55:33.000 --> 55:36.000
can't be as effective

55:36.000 --> 55:39.000
as they were a few years ago.

55:39.000 --> 55:42.000
That's why coaching can help.

55:42.000 --> 55:45.000
It's really easy.

55:45.000 --> 55:48.000
You ask questions, get answers

55:48.000 --> 55:51.000
and change your actions.

55:51.000 --> 55:54.000
But that's what you should strive for.

55:54.000 --> 55:57.000
It's the non-directive approach

55:57.000 --> 56:00.000
that makes the shift from the directive

56:00.000 --> 56:03.000
to the place of instructions.

56:03.000 --> 56:06.000
Questions.

56:06.000 --> 56:09.000
Questions that can stimulate

56:09.000 --> 56:12.000
both the leaders, employees and the organization.

56:15.000 --> 56:18.000
Next.

56:18.000 --> 56:21.000
I'd like to move on to the topic of goals.

56:21.000 --> 56:24.000
The goal in the organization.

56:24.000 --> 56:27.000
The goal set by the leader.

56:27.000 --> 56:30.000
The goal that the whole team will strive for.

56:31.000 --> 56:34.000
So, if we talk about

56:34.000 --> 56:37.000
the goal set by the leader

56:37.000 --> 56:40.000
the first question to ask is

56:40.000 --> 56:43.000
what do you want to achieve?

56:43.000 --> 56:46.000
What result do you want to achieve?

56:46.000 --> 56:49.000
These are questions that

56:49.000 --> 56:52.000
are constantly in the leader's head.

56:52.000 --> 56:55.000
How do I achieve a certain goal?

56:55.000 --> 56:58.000
How do I achieve a certain goal?

56:59.000 --> 57:02.000
How do I reach a new level of profitability?

57:02.000 --> 57:05.000
How do I expand my influence?

57:05.000 --> 57:08.000
How do I take a bigger share in the market?

57:08.000 --> 57:11.000
All of this is really important.

57:11.000 --> 57:14.000
But what happens next?

57:14.000 --> 57:17.000
Usually, everyone acts

57:17.000 --> 57:20.000
based on their past experience.

57:20.000 --> 57:23.000
Last year I did this and that.

57:23.000 --> 57:26.000
I'll do it now.

57:27.000 --> 57:30.000
But the actions I did last year

57:30.000 --> 57:33.000
will lead to the same success.

57:33.000 --> 57:36.000
Maybe they will, maybe they won't.

57:36.000 --> 57:39.000
So, you need to define your goal clearly.

57:39.000 --> 57:42.000
Remember how it was with Ivan Tsarevich

57:42.000 --> 57:45.000
and Zmei Gorynych.

57:45.000 --> 57:48.000
The clear goal should be so clear

57:48.000 --> 57:51.000
so clear that there is no thought

57:51.000 --> 57:54.000
that you can strive for something else.

57:55.000 --> 57:58.000
We achieve what we pay more attention to.

58:02.000 --> 58:05.000
So, in coaching there is a concept

58:05.000 --> 58:08.000
called the final result format.

58:08.000 --> 58:11.000
Of course, you are familiar with the basic blocks

58:11.000 --> 58:14.000
of this format.

58:14.000 --> 58:17.000
I'll give you a brief description.

58:17.000 --> 58:20.000
The first thing you need in the final result format

58:20.000 --> 58:23.000
as a method of building goals

58:23.000 --> 58:26.000
is to formulate this goal positively.

58:26.000 --> 58:29.000
What is positive?

58:29.000 --> 58:32.000
If we talk about the goal of improvement

58:32.000 --> 58:35.000
of a department or a company

58:35.000 --> 58:38.000
then this goal is

58:38.000 --> 58:41.000
a new market

58:41.000 --> 58:44.000
or a goal of achieving new effects

58:44.000 --> 58:47.000
or a new product market.

58:47.000 --> 58:50.000
But this is not a goal

58:50.000 --> 58:53.000
that we say

58:53.000 --> 58:56.000
we don't want to lag behind anymore

58:56.000 --> 58:59.000
we don't want to be lazy anymore

58:59.000 --> 59:02.000
we don't want to be late anymore.

59:02.000 --> 59:05.000
This is not a goal.

59:05.000 --> 59:08.000
This is more like a complaint

59:08.000 --> 59:11.000
that we won't work with.

59:11.000 --> 59:14.000
The goal here is

59:14.000 --> 59:17.000
what we want.

59:17.000 --> 59:20.000
And the goal is stated in the terms of the future.

59:20.000 --> 59:23.000
This is a goal that is

59:23.000 --> 59:26.000
a little bit ahead.

59:26.000 --> 59:29.000
This is a goal that we will reach.

59:29.000 --> 59:32.000
So, in short

59:32.000 --> 59:35.000
the goal is to bring the company to a new level.

59:35.000 --> 59:38.000
The goal is to increase the income.

59:38.000 --> 59:41.000
The goal is to bring a new product.

59:41.000 --> 59:44.000
These are goals that are formulated positively.

59:45.000 --> 59:48.000
The second point

59:48.000 --> 59:51.000
that is a component of the final result

59:51.000 --> 59:54.000
is that it is important

59:54.000 --> 59:57.000
that this goal is within your control.

59:57.000 --> 01:00:00.000
So that the goal you set

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:03.000
you can achieve it.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:06.000
So that its achievement depends on you

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:09.000
as a leader.

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:12.000
Because if we set a goal

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:16.000
that for some reason

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:19.000
we can't control now

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:22.000
then its probability of achieving it is really small.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:25.000
A leader, when setting a certain goal

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:28.000
must mean

01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:31.000
what he can control.

01:00:31.000 --> 01:00:34.000
And in no case choose goals

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:37.000
that are not under his control.

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:40.000
If we talk about middle managers

01:00:40.000 --> 01:00:43.000
not everyone can be controlled by the resources of the organization.

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:46.000
Not everyone can sign certain documents.

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:49.000
Not every leader can be

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:52.000
financed.

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:55.000
So if we set a certain goal

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:58.000
then we need to think about

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:01.000
whether it is within my control

01:01:01.000 --> 01:01:04.000
or within the control of my employees.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:07.000
And they have access to all the necessary resources.

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:11.000
And it is very important here

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:14.000
even if this goal is not under your control

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:17.000
think about how you can

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:20.000
transfer what is not under your control

01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:23.000
to the control zone.

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:26.000
Let's say

01:01:26.000 --> 01:01:29.000
if at this moment

01:01:29.000 --> 01:01:32.000
you don't have access to certain documents

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:35.000
that are necessary for changes

01:01:35.000 --> 01:01:38.000
what can you do to get access to them?

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:41.000
What specific steps should be taken

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:44.000
to get these documents

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:47.000
or this information?

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:50.000
So the second very important point

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:53.000
is the goal within my control

01:01:53.000 --> 01:01:56.000
at least 50%.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:59.000
If this is not the case

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:02.000
then we won't be able to work

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:05.000
within the control zone.

01:02:05.000 --> 01:02:08.000
Next, probably everyone knows

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:11.000
the formula SMART.

01:02:11.000 --> 01:02:14.000
We won't dwell on it in detail

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:17.000
we will just comment on it.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:20.000
SMART is the ability to set smart goals

