01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:41.000
So, in your feedback,

01:18:41.000 --> 01:18:44.000
for example, for an employee,

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:47.000
use the following model.

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:50.000
First, analyze the employee's actions.

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:53.000
What did he do?

01:18:53.000 --> 01:18:56.000
And how well did he do this job?

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:59.000
This is an analysis of his activity.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:02.000
Next, what is the effect

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:05.000
of the work that the employee did?

01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:08.000
And the next point is,

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:11.000
what can be improved here?

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:14.000
What can be done better next time?

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:17.000
What can be done better next time

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:20.000
to avoid possible mistakes

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:23.000
and to do something more effective

01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:26.000
and more effective?

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:29.000
Think about it.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:32.000
If you give feedback to your employee

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:35.000
and say,

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:38.000
what did you do

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:41.000
in your actions at the exhibition?

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:44.000
You were standing at the stand,

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:47.000
you were talking to the visitors,

01:19:47.000 --> 01:19:50.000
you were giving out booklets.

01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:53.000
Great! What is the effect of your activity?

01:19:53.000 --> 01:19:56.000
Most likely, the answer is the following.

01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:59.000
I gave out so many booklets,

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:02.000
I talked to so many people.

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:05.000
And what else?

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:08.000
What is the result?

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:11.000
What can you do better next time?

01:20:11.000 --> 01:20:14.000
How can you show yourself in a different way

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:17.000
to achieve more effect?

01:20:17.000 --> 01:20:20.000
How else can you show yourself?

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:23.000
If you just stand at the stand

01:20:23.000 --> 01:20:26.000
and give out booklets,

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:29.000
what else can you do?

01:20:29.000 --> 01:20:32.000
Talk to people who visit this exhibition,

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:35.000
maybe.

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:38.000
It is known that some people even sign contracts

01:20:38.000 --> 01:20:41.000
at the exhibition.

01:20:41.000 --> 01:20:44.000
There is no limit to perfection.

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:47.000
You should always think about your feedback,

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:50.000
what can be improved.

01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:53.000
These are three basic blocks

01:20:53.000 --> 01:20:56.000
of developing feedback.

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:59.000
As a rule, the effect of feedback

01:20:59.000 --> 01:21:02.000
is the employee's inspiration,

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:05.000
what can he do differently from the critics?

01:21:05.000 --> 01:21:08.000
If the employee is criticized,

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:11.000
if he is told that he did everything wrong,

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:14.000
does he have a desire to do something else?

01:21:14.000 --> 01:21:17.000
Most likely, no.

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:20.000
If you go the other way,

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:23.000
if you give the employee a developing feedback,

01:21:23.000 --> 01:21:26.000
you will notice how inspired he is.

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:29.000
It is really so.

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:32.000
The employee will be grateful to you

01:21:32.000 --> 01:21:35.000
for your hard work,

01:21:35.000 --> 01:21:38.000
for your opinion,

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:41.000
for your interest in what he can do better.

01:21:41.000 --> 01:21:44.000
Of course, all this should happen

01:21:44.000 --> 01:21:47.000
in a system of normal relationships,

01:21:47.000 --> 01:21:50.000
relationships of trust and openness.

01:21:50.000 --> 01:21:53.000
The employees also have a feeling

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:56.000
that they are appreciated,

01:21:56.000 --> 01:21:59.000
that they are needed.

01:21:59.000 --> 01:22:02.000
If the management is interested in my work,

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:05.000
if the management is so attentive to my work,

01:22:05.000 --> 01:22:08.000
they appreciate me, they value me.

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:11.000
This is also an important factor

01:22:11.000 --> 01:22:14.000
of the loyalty of our staff.

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:17.000
And the last question we ask the employee is

01:22:17.000 --> 01:22:20.000
what can you do better?

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:23.000
Maybe I can help you with something.

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:26.000
These questions really stimulate

01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:29.000
this employee to do something better,

01:22:29.000 --> 01:22:32.000
to find some ways

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:35.000
how I can act better,

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:38.000
how I can show myself better.

01:22:38.000 --> 01:22:41.000
Accordingly, the employee who has improved something

01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:44.000
feels joy,

01:22:44.000 --> 01:22:47.000
feels pride for himself,

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:50.000
for his work.

01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:53.000
And the employee who has improved something

01:22:53.000 --> 01:22:56.000
feels pride for himself.

01:22:56.000 --> 01:22:59.000
Will this employee want to work with you further?

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:02.000
He will.

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:05.000
Any person wants recognition

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:08.000
and any person wants positive feedback.

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:11.000
Accordingly, feedback is a really powerful tool.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:14.000
It is really worth using.

01:23:14.000 --> 01:23:17.000
Coaching of the subordinate

01:23:17.000 --> 01:23:20.000
Coaching of the subordinate

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.000
Now our topic is

01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:26.000
coaching of the subordinate.

01:23:26.000 --> 01:23:29.000
What can we say here?

01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:32.000
When do we need coaching of the subordinate?

01:23:32.000 --> 01:23:35.000
We have already talked about

01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:38.000
what type of employee needs coaching.

01:23:38.000 --> 01:23:41.000
Most likely, it is not worth involving

01:23:41.000 --> 01:23:44.000
the employee who has just joined our company.

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:47.000
The employee who needs to adapt

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:50.000
and get some knowledge

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:53.000
and skills of working in this system.

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:56.000
and get some knowledge and skills of working in this system.

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:59.000
Most likely, coaching is necessary for employees

01:23:59.000 --> 01:24:02.000
who are already in the business,

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:05.000
who are ready to work.

01:24:05.000 --> 01:24:08.000
And here we need to understand

01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:11.000
which employee needs this support

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:14.000
and which does not.

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:17.000
Maybe there are employees who are doing great without coaching

01:24:17.000 --> 01:24:20.000
who are already working well

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:23.000
and there is no need to change anything.

01:24:23.000 --> 01:24:26.000
and there is no need to change anything.

01:24:26.000 --> 01:24:29.000
Look at your subordinates.

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:32.000
Maybe some of them need this feedback

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:35.000
and need coaching.

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:38.000
Look at your subordinates who are ready to grow

01:24:38.000 --> 01:24:41.000
and who need this help and support

01:24:41.000 --> 01:24:44.000
and look at their abilities

01:24:44.000 --> 01:24:47.000
and you will be of help

01:24:47.000 --> 01:24:50.000
not only to this person,

01:24:50.000 --> 01:24:53.000
but to the whole company.

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:56.000
When one employee's potential grows

01:24:56.000 --> 01:24:59.000
it can have an impact on the whole company's potential

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:02.000
because his actions lead to the success of the whole company.

01:25:03.000 --> 01:25:06.000
Of course, if you see that the employee

01:25:06.000 --> 01:25:09.000
is on the contrary, maybe a bit lazy

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:12.000
or somehow started to work worse than before

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:15.000
you should also pay attention to him

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:18.000
and ask him some coaching questions.

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:24.000
What's going on?

01:25:24.000 --> 01:25:27.000
Maybe you are missing something?

01:25:27.000 --> 01:25:30.000
Maybe you need to do something now?

01:25:30.000 --> 01:25:33.000
Or what can I do for you?

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:36.000
Such employees who are a bit lazy

01:25:36.000 --> 01:25:39.000
also need our attention

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:42.000
because they have such a great potential

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:45.000
as well as the employees who are ahead of their time.

01:25:45.000 --> 01:25:48.000
And our task is to develop this potential in them.

01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:51.000
And it's worth coaching these employees too.

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:54.000
What do we need to do?

01:25:54.000 --> 01:25:57.000
What do we need to do?

01:25:57.000 --> 01:26:00.000
What do we need to do?

01:26:00.000 --> 01:26:03.000
What can you use to determine

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:06.000
which employee needs coaching?

01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:09.000
The first and quite obvious measurement

01:26:09.000 --> 01:26:12.000
is the assessment results

01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:15.000
and assessment results,

01:26:15.000 --> 01:26:18.000
maybe annual.

01:26:18.000 --> 01:26:21.000
If you look at these results

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:24.000
you will probably understand

01:26:24.000 --> 01:26:27.000
who should be touched

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:30.000
and who should really do coaching.

01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:33.000
One of the factors is regular meetings.

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:36.000
You meet with your employees,

01:26:36.000 --> 01:26:39.000
you communicate with people

01:26:39.000 --> 01:26:42.000
and you can understand perfectly well

01:26:42.000 --> 01:26:45.000
that one of them is active,

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:48.000
successful

01:26:48.000 --> 01:26:51.000
and the other one is not very active.

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:54.000
If a person is not very active

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:57.000
it's worth paying attention to him.

01:26:57.000 --> 01:27:00.000
Of course, one of the important functions

01:27:00.000 --> 01:27:03.000
of a coach as a leader

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:06.000
is observance.

01:27:06.000 --> 01:27:09.000
Observe your employees.

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:12.000
Observe what's going on with them.

01:27:12.000 --> 01:27:15.000
Maybe something has changed.

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:18.000
If you notice and correct all these changes

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:22.000
the success of the whole company

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:25.000
and your personal success

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:28.000
will be much more natural.

01:27:28.000 --> 01:27:31.000
Pay attention to this.

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:34.000
Let's look at the probability

01:27:34.000 --> 01:27:37.000
of a positive result from coaching

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:40.000
for some of our subordinates.

01:27:40.000 --> 01:27:43.000
Pay attention to how often

01:27:43.000 --> 01:27:46.000
the behavior that requires correction

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:50.000
is changing.

01:27:50.000 --> 01:27:53.000
As you have already noticed,

01:27:53.000 --> 01:27:56.000
maybe some of your subordinates

01:27:56.000 --> 01:27:59.000
became less effective.

01:27:59.000 --> 01:28:02.000
Maybe some of the people

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:05.000
paid less attention to the important tasks

01:28:05.000 --> 01:28:08.000
of the company.

01:28:08.000 --> 01:28:11.000
Or maybe a salesman from the sales department

01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:14.000
who used to be a winner

01:28:14.000 --> 01:28:17.000
and now has bad results.

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:20.000
What he sells now

01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:23.000
may not be what he is capable of.

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:26.000
The second axis is how deep

01:28:26.000 --> 01:28:29.000
the cause of this behavior lies.

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:32.000
Pay attention to this.

01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:35.000
If this behavior is rare

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:38.000
and it's just a reaction

01:28:38.000 --> 01:28:41.000
to a particular situation

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:44.000
it's easy to change it

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:47.000
even with the help of coaching methods.

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:50.000
But if this behavior

01:28:50.000 --> 01:28:53.000
is often shown

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:56.000
and you notice that it's a manifestation

01:28:56.000 --> 01:28:59.000
of this person's character

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:02.000
it will be difficult to change it

01:29:02.000 --> 01:29:05.000
even if it's not possible at all.

01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:08.000
Such characteristics should be

01:29:08.000 --> 01:29:11.000
considered by HR services

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:14.000
when they hire a person.

01:29:14.000 --> 01:29:17.000
They should consider the characteristics

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:20.000
and behavioral functions

01:29:20.000 --> 01:29:23.000
that this person has,

01:29:23.000 --> 01:29:26.000
values and beliefs.

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:29.000
In accordance with this

01:29:29.000 --> 01:29:32.000
coaching should be done.

01:29:32.000 --> 01:29:35.000
For a beginner coaching manager

01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:38.000
it's easier to work with people

01:29:38.000 --> 01:29:41.000
who were in the first square.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:44.000
The behavior that is needed

01:29:44.000 --> 01:29:47.000
in the correction is not shown often

01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:50.000
and it's not characteristic of this person.

01:29:50.000 --> 01:29:53.000
It's a kind of a surge.

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:56.000
Then it's easy to adjust it

01:29:56.000 --> 01:29:59.000
even for beginners.

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:02.000
Let's move on to the next topic.

01:30:02.000 --> 01:30:05.000
Our topic is called

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:08.000
Coaching of a Manager.

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:11.000
The coaching of a manager

01:30:11.000 --> 01:30:14.000
differs from the coaching of a subordinate.

01:30:14.000 --> 01:30:17.000
Here a professional coach

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:20.000
and a manager are in a partnership.

01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:23.000
Here a coach will ask

01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:26.000
such questions to a manager.

01:30:26.000 --> 01:30:29.000
What is the purpose of the change?

01:30:30.000 --> 01:30:33.000
Why is it valuable and important for the company?

01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:36.000
What results do you want to achieve?

01:30:36.000 --> 01:30:39.000
What role does the coach play here?

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:42.000
It's perfectly clear that

01:30:42.000 --> 01:30:45.000
if the goal is to increase the profit,

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:48.000
then within half an hour

01:30:48.000 --> 01:30:51.000
during which the coach works with the manager

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:54.000
this goal will not be achieved.

01:30:54.000 --> 01:30:57.000
The result of this change

01:30:58.000 --> 01:31:01.000
will be a plan,

01:31:01.000 --> 01:31:04.000
a clear goal,

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:07.000
clear steps to this goal,

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:10.000
motivation,

01:31:10.000 --> 01:31:13.000
and the power to act.

01:31:13.000 --> 01:31:16.000
But not the increase of the profit.

01:31:16.000 --> 01:31:19.000
Here is a distribution of responsibility.

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:22.000
The coach is responsible for

01:31:22.000 --> 01:31:25.000
building up the coaching process,

01:31:26.000 --> 01:31:29.000
to ask the necessary questions

01:31:29.000 --> 01:31:32.000
and get answers from the manager.

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:37.000
But the management takes the implementation

01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:40.000
of this plan and strategy on itself.

01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:45.000
And here is only the support

01:31:45.000 --> 01:31:48.000
feedback from the coach

01:31:48.000 --> 01:31:51.000
at a certain point.

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:54.000
What did you achieve now?

01:31:54.000 --> 01:31:57.000
How do I evaluate it?

01:31:57.000 --> 01:32:00.000
Is it good enough?

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:03.000
Yes, I can move on.

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:06.000
Or what I achieved now is not good enough?

01:32:06.000 --> 01:32:09.000
Then maybe I should go back a little

01:32:09.000 --> 01:32:12.000
and see what went wrong.

01:32:12.000 --> 01:32:15.000
What happened here that

01:32:15.000 --> 01:32:18.000
did not allow this result to manifest?

01:32:18.000 --> 01:32:21.000
And the tasks that the managers

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:24.000
want to solve for themselves with coaching

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:27.000
could be the following.

01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:30.000
It can be communication improvement

01:32:30.000 --> 01:32:33.000
with the managers and employees.

01:32:33.000 --> 01:32:36.000
It can even be presentation skills,

01:32:36.000 --> 01:32:39.000
communication skills with people.

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:42.000
It is really an important point for the manager.

01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:45.000
It can also be a request to improve

01:32:45.000 --> 01:32:48.000
their management skills,

01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:51.000
planning, organization and control.

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:54.000
It is also an important point for the manager.

01:32:54.000 --> 01:32:57.000
After all, the manager,

01:32:57.000 --> 01:33:00.000
while being continuously in the process

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:03.000
of managing the organization,

01:33:03.000 --> 01:33:06.000
performs many functions.

01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:09.000
And each of them he must perform efficiently.

01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:12.000
Naturally, we support the manager in this.

01:33:12.000 --> 01:33:15.000
We stimulate and guide them.

01:33:15.000 --> 01:33:18.000
Naturally, the potential of a person,

01:33:18.000 --> 01:33:21.000
the potential of a leader is needed in this recovery.

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:24.000
Some managers ask me

01:33:24.000 --> 01:33:27.000
about the consideration of a mission

01:33:27.000 --> 01:33:30.000
and vision for their company.

01:33:30.000 --> 01:33:33.000
In one case,

01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:36.000
a manager of a well-known company

01:33:36.000 --> 01:33:39.000
invited us to his office

01:33:39.000 --> 01:33:42.000
and said,

01:33:42.000 --> 01:33:45.000
Our mission is already formed.

01:33:45.000 --> 01:33:48.000
Do you have it already?

01:33:48.000 --> 01:33:51.000
Yes, it is already formed.

01:33:51.000 --> 01:33:54.000
It is in the upper drawer of my table.

01:33:54.000 --> 01:33:57.000
What is it like?

01:33:57.000 --> 01:34:00.000
I don't remember. I'll get it and see.

01:34:00.000 --> 01:34:03.000
Is it a mission if a person doesn't remember it

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:06.000
and doesn't know how it is formulated?

01:34:06.000 --> 01:34:09.000
It is unlikely.

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:12.000
What is really important,

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:15.000
what stimulates and moves,

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:18.000
just like vision,

01:34:18.000 --> 01:34:21.000
is that a manager must have a vision

01:34:21.000 --> 01:34:24.000
of what he is going to,

01:34:24.000 --> 01:34:27.000
what he leads the whole organization to.

01:34:27.000 --> 01:34:30.000
If a person has this vision,

01:34:30.000 --> 01:34:33.000
if he already knows what result he wants to achieve,

01:34:33.000 --> 01:34:36.000
then he can inspire and guide his subordinates.

01:34:36.000 --> 01:34:39.000
If he doesn't know what he is moving to,

01:34:39.000 --> 01:34:42.000
who can he inspire?

01:34:42.000 --> 01:34:45.000
Can he do it at all?

